column4: p. 56 mentions various numbers, but some are not about the whole company. We also don't know if 57,084 refers to scope 1. AUch "supply chain emissions" macht stutzig. Angaben im Report widersprechen sich und lassen sich nicht klar den Scopes zuordnen. p. 45 "In FY2020/3, the amount of CO₂ emitted from Morinaga’s four factories and five affiliated production com-panies was 57,048 t-CO. [...] The amount of CO₂ emitted from over overseas production facilities in 2019 was 9,137 t-CO₂. (p. 45). P. 44 nennt zusätzlich die Zahl 19 512. Tabelle auf S. 56 nennt weitere, andere Zahlen. Reference Guidelines sind auf S. 60 angegeben, aber keine der von uns gesuchten. not sure what reporting standard
column8: Starting from the convention that we take reported total scope values as correct, if there are no other disaggregated values (by subsidiaries, business lines etc),we would annotate the p.56 as correct. However, there are important limitations as mentioned by annotator 2 that ideally would also be extracted for context
column44: We agree with annotator 1, the numbers referenced by annotator 2 refer to the Scope 1 to 3 totals and in our opinion check out, no issue
